    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nSort/reformat imports code action from purescript-language-server crashes in Neovim with attempt to index local 'workspace_edit' (a userdata value).\n\nSteps:\n1. Open a PureScript file with imports in Neovim with purescript-language-server attached.\n2. Save the file first (this is required for purescriptls code actions to appear).\n3. Run vim.lsp.buf.code_action().\n4. Select \"Sort/reformat imports\".\n\nError:\n```\nCode actions:\n1: Blame line [null-ls]\n2: Sort/reformat imports [purescriptls]\nType number and <Enter> or click with the mouse (q or empty cancels): 2\nvim.schedule callback: ...unwrapped-0.12.2/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/util.lua:700: attempt to index local 'workspace_edit' (a userdata value)\nstack traceback:\n        ...unwrapped-0.12.2/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/util.lua:700: in function 'apply_workspace_edit'\n        ...-unwrapped-0.12.2/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/buf.lua:1252: in function 'apply_action'\n        ...-unwrapped-0.12.2/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/buf.lua:1309: in function 'on_choice'\n        ...eovim-unwrapped-0.12.2/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/ui.lua:58: in function 'select'\n        ...-unwrapped-0.12.2/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/buf.lua:1342: in function 'on_code_action_results'\n        ...-unwrapped-0.12.2/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/buf.lua:1417: in function 'handler'\n        ...ovim-unwrapped-0.12.2/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp.lua:1297: in function 'handler'\n        ...wrapped-0.12.2/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/client.lua:742: in function ''\n        vim/_core/editor.lua: in function <vim/_core/editor.lua:0>\n```\n\n### Steps to reproduce using \"nvim --clean -u minimal_init.lua\"\n\n```lua\nlocal pattern = 'purescript'\nlocal cmd = {'purescript-language-server', '--stdio'}\nlocal root_markers = {'.git', 'spago.dhall', 'flake.nix', 'packages.dhall'}\n\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd('FileType', {\n  pattern = pattern,\n  callback = function(args)\n    local match = vim.fs.find(root_markers, { path = args.file, upward = true })[1]\n    local root_dir = match and vim.fn.fnamemodify(match, ':h') or nil\n    vim.lsp.start({\n      name = 'purescriptls',\n      cmd = cmd,\n      root_dir = root_dir,\n    })\n  end\n})\n\nvim.keymap.set('n', '<leader>ca', vim.lsp.buf.code_action, { buffer = true })\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n_No response_\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.12.2\n\n### Language server name/version\n\npurescript-language-server  0.18.5\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nLinux (NixOS)\n\n### Log file\n\n_No response_",
