        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> But we should show a better error message if we can.\n\n@justinmk I'm all for a nicer UX, but handling an invalid LSP response feels unnecessarily defensive. We don't do this in other LSP methods were a result or property is documented as not nil.",
