        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> We don't do this in other LSP methods were a result or property is documented as not nil.\n\nI think we do in some cases, but even if not, whenever a case is reported, that tells us a real-world situation where we can add a 1-line assert. That is worthwhile, because it saves time not only for users, but also for us, since it will reduce bug reports or make them easy to triage.",
